fixed_allocation","heading":"Fixed Allocation","priceDescription":"Estimated cost of investing over the next 12 months (assuming returns of 0%)","costs":[{"feeType":"nutmeg","investmentCostsText":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Nutmeg fees\nincluding VAT where applicable\n0.75% up to £100k\n0.35% on portion beyond","spans":[{"start":0,"end":12,"type":"strong"},{"start":43,"end":48,"type":"strong"},{"start":43,"end":47,"type":"label","data":{"label":"rate"}},{"start":56,"end":59,"type":"label","data":{"label":"threshold"}},{"start":61,"end":66,"type":"strong"},{"start":61,"end":65,"type":"label","data":{"label":"promotion"}}]}]},{"feeType":"fund_cost","investmentCostsText":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Fund costs\n0.19%","spans":[{"start":0,"end":16,"type":"strong"},{"start":11,"end":15,"type":"label","data":{"label":"etf"}}]}]},{"feeType":"marketing_spread","investmentCostsText":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Market spread\n0.08%","spans":[{"start":0,"end":19,"type":"strong"},{"start":14,"end":18,"type":"label","data":{"label":"spread"}}]}]}]}]},{"type":"rich_text","text":[{"type":"image","url":"https://images.prismic.io/nutmegnewbrand/5a33f6e6-0ddc-41ce-9b76-e5799ebd1cbc_Waves.png?auto=compress,format","alt":null,"copyright":null,"dimensions":{"width":100,"height":50}}],"spacing":"default","alignment":"center","backrgoundColor":"white","noStack":false,"id":null},{"type":"faq","heading":{"text":"Most people ask us…","level":"1"},"cta":null,"isOpen":false,"sections":[{"primaryLabel":{"text":"What’s the difference between fixed allocation and fully managed?","level":"3"},"secondaryLabel":null,"text":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"If you prefer lower costs for your investments, then fixed allocation might be for you. However, if you want an investment professional to watch over your investments with the ability to make changes on a daily basis, then you might consider fully managed.","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"In terms of how they’re designed, the fixed allocation portfolios have a backward-looking perspective. They are constructed with the implicit assumption that past long-term market behaviour will be repeated in the future over the long term, although, as with all investment, this is not a guarantee.","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Fully managed portfolios have a forward-looking perspective, with the investment team making decisions about market value, market momentum, prevailing cyclical and structural forces expected to impact in the near to medium term. The investment team learns from past behaviour, but is not tied to it.","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"These differences in investment perspective and portfolio flexibility help to explain asset allocation differences between fixed and fully managed portfolios and the resulting short and medium-term portfolio returns.","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":" ","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Fixed allocation portfolios are cheaper than fully managed because they are an off-the-shelf investment product that does not require daily management by our investment team. Fully managed portfolios cost more than fixed allocation ones because they are an investment service, overseen and managed by Nutmeg’s experienced investment team.","spans":[]}]},{"primaryLabel":{"text":"Why do fixed allocation portfolios cost less than fully managed?","level":"3"},"secondaryLabel":null,"text":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Fixed allocation portfolios are cheaper than fully managed because they are an off-the-shelf investment product that does not require daily management by our investment team. Fully managed portfolios cost more than fixed allocation ones because they are an investment service, overseen and managed by Nutmeg’s experienced investment team.","spans":[]}]},{"primaryLabel":{"text":"How do the Nutmeg investment team measure risk?","level":"3"},"secondaryLabel":null,"text":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Because of the way they are built, the fixed allocation portfolios can be seen as based on historical performance, since the mix of investments in the portfolio reflects past market conditions. Offsetting this risk is the fact that the Nutmeg team update the fixed allocations once a year based on the last year’s data. The annual review is an opportunity to add new asset classes that may emerge or to replace an ETF with a better performing substitute. ","spans":[]}]}]},{"type":"rich_text","text":[{"type":"image","url":"https://images.prismic.io/nutmegnewbrand/57c457ca-ff31-4340-a713-6ff28624ce96_Lines.png?auto=compress,format","alt":null,"copyright":null,"dimensions":{"width":100,"height":50}}],"spacing":"default","alignment":"center","backrgoundColor":"white","noStack":true,"id":null}],"seo":{"title":"Fixed allocation portfolios - passive investing - Nutmeg","description":"Fixed allocation portfolios offer passive investing with global, multi-asset allocation, fully-automated rebalancing and dividend reinvestment.","canonical":"/fixed-allocation-portfolios","image":null,"url":null,"metaTags":[]},"documentId":"YTtrkBAAACIAvI-3","type":"page_portfolio","headerMenu":{"items":[{"link":{"title":"Products"},"sections":[{"link":{"href":"/isas","title":"Stocks and shares ISA"},"links":[{"isExternal":false,"href":"https://api.nutmeg.com/onboarding/start","title":"Open a Nutmeg ISA"},{"isExternal":false,"href":"/isas/what-is-an-isa#what-is-an-isa","title":"What is an ISA?"},{"href":"/isas/transfer","title":"Transfer an ISA to Nutmeg"},{"href":"/isas/tax-benefits-of-isas","title":"ISA Benefits"},{"href":"/isa-calculator","title":"ISA Calculator"}],"text":""},{"link":{"href":"/lifetime-isa","title":"Stocks and shares Lifetime ISA"},"links":[{"isExternal":false,"href":"https://api.nutmeg.com/onboarding/start","title":"Open a Lifetime ISA"},{"isExternal":false,"href":"/lifetime-isa/lifetime-isa-faq#what-is-t